******
[3] Cholera - Congo DR (South Kivu)
Date: Tue 13 Jan 2015
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine trans., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/sante/2015/01/13/sud-kivu-14-cas-de-cholera-enregistres-kiliba/


Physician director of the hospital center of Kiliba [South Kivu], Dr Jean-Paul Buseni, said 14 cases of cholera, including a death, have been recorded at Kiliba (South Kivu) since last Sat 10 Jan 2015. The chief doctor of the area of health of Ruzizi [South Kivu], Dr Eric Muhubiri Namihaba, explains the resurgence of cholera by the breakdown in drinking water in the city of Kiliba for 2 months.

To cope with this situation, the area of health of Ruzizi account intends to begin the chlorination of water, while at the same time continuing the care of the sick.

